id.description: The ID used to identify this component in Dash callbacks.

setProps.description:
Dash-assigned callback that should be called to report property changes
to Dash, to make them available for callbacks.

data.description: The DataFrame of data that is to be displayed in the table

columns.description:
An array of objects: {name: str, id: str} used for display and
identification of columns in the table for calling setProps

page_current.description: A value used pretty much only for pagination purposes

total_results.description: A value used pretty much only for pagination purposes

page_size.description: A value used pretty much only for pagination purposes

location.description:
Needed because it is passed up to Dash to update the map
after a row is clicked in the table

report_number.description:
Needed because it is passed up to Dash to update the map
after a row is clicked in the table

column.description: The column that is being sorted, if sorting is active

ascending.description: Whether the sort is ascending (1), descending (-1), or none (0)
